{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reform the General Election System to Allow Direct Voting for Political Parties",
        "additional_details": "Under this system, each voter would cast a single vote for their preferred political party, and parliamentary seats would be allocated based on the overall share of the national vote.\r\n\r\nWe believe this reform would:\r\n\u2022 Ensure every vote counts equally, better reflecting the will of the people.\r\n\u2022 Make elections clearer and fairer by focusing on party leadership and policies rather than local constituency boundaries.\r\n\r\nWe urge the Government to consider and implement this change to improve democratic representation in the UK.",
        "background": "We call on the UK Government to introduce legislation to reform the electoral system so that citizens vote directly for a political party to lead the country, rather than for individual candidates in constituencies.",
